mcp (1.27.1-0ubuntu1~ppa1~noble2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Soften the pydantic runtime floor from `>= 2.11` to `>= 2.6` in both
    the pyproject patch and `debian/control`. The Avalan PPA's pydantic
    is capped at 2.6.4 by Noble's rustc 1.75 / maturin 1.3.2 toolchain
    (which caps pydantic-core at 2.16.3); mcp's eagerly-loaded modules
    reach only `BaseModel`, `ConfigDict`, `Field`, `RootModel`,
    `AnyUrl`, `UrlConstraints`, `FileUrl`, `TypeAdapter`,
    `validate_call`, and `ValidationError`, all stable since pydantic
    2.0. Without this softening, apt-get install of the Avalan chain
    failed with held-broken packages.

 -- Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>  Thu, 21 May 2026 18:00:00 -0300

mcp (1.27.1-0ubuntu1~ppa1~noble1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of mcp 1.27.1 for the Avalan PPA.
  * Runtime dep of Avalan's `server` extras. Not in Debian; the upstream
    sdist pulls `uv-dynamic-versioning` at build time and a handful of
    runtime dependencies (`pydantic-settings`, `sse-starlette`) that
    Noble's archive does not carry, so we hand-package from PyPI.
  * Ship a quilt patch (pyproject-for-noble) that switches the
    `[tool.hatch.version]` source from `uv-dynamic-versioning` to a
    static `version = "1.27.1"` so Noble's python3-hatchling builds the
    wheel without the unreleased uv helper, drops the
    `pydantic-settings` and `sse-starlette` runtime deps that are not in
    Noble (FastMCP's HTTP transports become unusable; the JSON-RPC core
    Avalan exercises is unaffected), and softens floors that fall below
    Noble's archive (httpx, jsonschema, pyjwt, uvicorn, typing-inspection)
    without changing the API surface the eagerly-loaded modules use.
  * Ship a quilt patch (lazy-fastmcp-import) that swaps the eager
    `from .fastmcp import FastMCP` in `mcp/server/__init__.py` for a
    PEP 562 `__getattr__` shim so `import mcp` does not pull
    pydantic_settings / starlette / sse-starlette at module load. The
    public attribute (`mcp.server.FastMCP`) is preserved.
  * Ship a quilt patch (defer-typevar-default-annotations) that adds
    `from __future__ import annotations` to `mcp/client/session.py`,
    `mcp/client/experimental/task_handlers.py`, and
    `mcp/shared/progress.py`, plus spells out the third TypeVar
    explicitly at one runtime call site in
    `mcp/client/session.py:_received_request`. Noble's
    typing_extensions 4.10 carries the `default=` keyword on TypeVar
    but does not patch `Generic.__class_getitem__` to consult that
    default, so subscripting `RequestContext` with only two of its
    three type arguments at module import time raises TypeError. PEP
    563 string annotations sidestep the eager evaluation; the
    explicit third argument keeps the one runtime construction
    valid. Drop the patch once Noble ships typing_extensions >= 4.12.

 -- Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>  Wed, 20 May 2026 00:55:00 -0300
